@startuml sequence_concurrent_race
!theme plain
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center

title Concurrent Draw + Registration Race Condition

participant "Draw Request" as DRAW
participant "Register Request" as REG
database "PostgreSQL" as DB

note over DB: Raffle active\n3 participants\n0 drawn\n(entries open)

DRAW -> DB: BEGIN TX (draw)
REG -> DB: BEGIN TX (register)

DRAW -> DB: SELECT random undrawn\nFOR UPDATE SKIP LOCKED
DB --> DRAW: "Alice" (row locked)

REG -> DB: SELECT COUNT(*)\nWHERE is_drawn=true
note right: Sees 0 drawn\n(draw not yet committed)
DB --> REG: count = 0

DRAW -> DB: UPDATE isDrawn=true
DRAW -> DB: COMMIT
note over DB: Alice now drawn\ndrawnCount = 1

REG -> DB: INSERT participant "Dave"
note right: INSERT succeeds because\nREG's TX started before\ndraw committed.\nThis is acceptable under\nREAD COMMITTED.

note over DB
  In practice, the narrow window
  makes this extremely unlikely.
  The next registration attempt
  will see drawnCount > 0
  and be correctly rejected.
end note

@enduml
